<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Happen" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Happen,</orth> to come to pass: <bibl n="shak. ado 1.1.271" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 1, 271</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.4.64" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 4, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 1.3.125" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 3, 125</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 3.2.1" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 2, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.1.128" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 1, 128</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.1.6" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 1, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.1.25" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.406" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 2, 406</bibl>. <cit><quote>these --ed accidents,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.250" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. V, 250</bibl></cit>. With <emph>to</emph>: <cit><quote>what can h. to me?</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 3.1.122" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 1, 122</bibl></cit>. With an inf.: <cit><quote>to effect whatever I shall h. to devise,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 4.330" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 330</bibl></cit>. With a clause following: <cit><quote>how unluckily it --ed that I should purchase,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 3.2.52" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 2, 52</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>